    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Electronic Fishbowl</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Regina H Williams letter holds juxtaposition of Marshall Sella's May 21 article on reality-based television and Ian Fisher's article about starving Burundians highlights Americans' and Western Europeans' distorted values</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The juxtaposition of Sella's article about a frivolous indulgence of obsessed exhibitionists and Ian Fisher's ''Ethnic Fencing,'' about the starving people in Burundian concentration camps, points out better than words the distorted values a depressingly large number of bored, well-fed Americans and Western Europeans bring to their lives.</p>
        <p>Regina H. Williams</p>
        <p>Princeton, N.J.</p>
      </block>
